The paper presents an interface for building and customizing a Named Entity Recognition and Linking (NER+L) model for biomedical domain text. This falls under the category of Natural Language Processing (NLP) and Machine Learning (ML) applied to the biomedical domain. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions active learning, which is a popular technique in ML, suggesting cs.LG (Machine Learning) as another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the collection of supervised learning training data for researcher-specific use cases, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.CY (Computers and Society). Finally, the paper's focus on customizing the NER+L model for biomedical text suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as a possible sub-category.
